Subject: Skip wrapper class for single $ref allOf (deduplication)

When a property uses `allOf: [{$ref: X}]` (commonly with `nullable: true`)
without local properties of its own, Jane currently generates a duplicate
wrapper class for each property. The wrapper has identical structure to the
referenced schema, only its name differs.

This patch makes `AllOfGuesser::guessClass()` short-circuit when:
- allOf contains exactly one item,
- that item is a `Reference` (i.e. a pure `$ref`),
- the wrapping object has no local `properties`,
- the wrapping object has no `additionalProperties`.

In that case the wrapper is transparent and `guessType()` already routes the
property type to the referenced class via the chain guesser. Nullable info
stays on the property level (`Property::isNullable()`), so nullable getters
are preserved.

See janephp/janephp#535 for upstream context.

--- a/Guesser/JsonSchema/AllOfGuesser.php
+++ b/Guesser/JsonSchema/AllOfGuesser.php
@@ -36,6 +36,19 @@ class AllOfGuesser implements GuesserInterface, TypeGuesserInterface, ChainGuess
      */
     public function guessClass($object, string $name, string $reference, Registry $registry): void
     {
+        $allOfItems = $object->getAllOf();
+
+        // Прозрачная ссылка: allOf из одного $ref без локальных полей.
+        // Не создаём wrapper-класс — тип свойства будет разрезолвен через chainGuesser->guessType().
+        if (
+            \count($allOfItems) === 1
+            && $allOfItems[0] instanceof Reference
+            && (!method_exists($object, 'getProperties') || empty($object->getProperties()))
+            && (!method_exists($object, 'getAdditionalProperties') || $object->getAdditionalProperties() === null || $object->getAdditionalProperties() === false)
+        ) {
+            return;
+        }
+
         $hasSubObject = false;

         foreach ($object->getAllOf() as $allOf) {
